My key sources

(and widely recognized guides)

Overview

Preregistration templates

  • In OSF (Van Den Akker et al., 2023)
  • PRISMA-P
  • PreregRS (Schneider et al., 2022)


Frameworks

see Kolaski et al. (2023), Table 2

Reasoning

  • On publication bias (e.g., incuding grey literature)
  • On recall and precision (see Cooper et al., 2019, Ch. 4.5)


Documentation

PRISMA-S


Checklist

Peer Review of Electronic Search Strategies (PRESS) (McGowan et al., 2016)

Frameworks

  • e.g., PICO
  • more see Kolaski et al. (2023), Table 2


Objectivity

Independent screening of 100% by at least 2 reviewers


Open Materials

Share screening manual with publication


Documentation

PRISMA flow diagram

Objectivity

Independent data extraction and coding of 100% by at least 2 reviewers


Open Materials

Share coding manual with publication

Primary studies

  • Randomized: Cochrane RoB 2
  • Non-randomized: ROBINS-I
  • Observational: STROBE


Open Code

FAIR and reproducible data analysis (Ziemann et al., 2023)


Synthesized findings

  • Investigate publication bias, sensitivity analysis
  • Cochrane GRADE

Reporting

  • PRISMA 2020 checklist
  • MARS (Appelbaum et al., 2018)


Open Data

  • Share data as open as possible with publication

Check yourself

Appraisal tool for systematic reviews: AMSTAR 2 (Shea et al., 2017)


Reproducibility

in research syntheses (Schneider & Heck, 2024, German)

  • Cooper (2017)
  • Cooper et al. (2019)
  • Cochrane Handbook for Systematic Reviews of Interventions
  • equator-network

Thank you!
